Program: Omnibus
Title: A Bird with no Name
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mdk
Last Broadcast Date: 23 April 2002
The violinist and amateur conservationist talks about her life-long love of birds all around the world. She discovered the new subspecies, Zoothera erythronota, while taking part in an observation exercise for Operation Walasea in Indonesia.